NATO prepares for summit uneasily, as US pressures fellow members
description: The US has urged its allies, which have limited financial resources, to ramp up defense spending. The demands come amid tighter control over NATO and a backdrop of dissension over how to approach the Russian threat.

From Peru to the Vatican, the rise of 'Monseñor Roberto de Chiclayo,' now Leo XIV
description: Francis's successor at the Vatican lived for many years in the South American country. Le Monde traveled to the city of Chiclayo to meet with several people who remember the days when he was still known as Robert Prevost.

headline: Refusing to become a manager is more common in France than elsewhere
description: According to an international survey by Cegos, a significant share of employees showed little interest in becoming managers, especially in France. The reasons include organizational culture, the image of the managerial role and the emergence of alternative models of professional success.

headline: 'Jaws' turns 50: A foundational film that changed cinema
description: The incredible success of Steven Spielberg's film, released simultaneously across the US at the very start of summer 1975, was the result of a wild gamble by Universal that revolutionized Hollywood, writes Le Monde's Michel Guerrin in his column.

headline: Finding inspiration for photography in the kitchen
description: From Irving Penn's frozen fruits and vegetables to Sabine Weiss's fish trap and the Blumes' flying crockery, kitchens, their utensils, and their ingredients have long inspired photographers. Striking images by some 30 artists add spice to the exhibition 'Dans ma cuisine' ('In My Kitchen'), on view through July 31 at Les Douches gallery in Paris.

description: Since the beginning of his term, Donald Trump has been applying Project 2025, a 922-page bible written by the conservative think tank. Today, its president, Kevin Roberts, is looking across the Atlantic. On a visit to France, he met with leaders of far-right parties.

headline: Guy Savoy, Michelin-starred chef: 'At 15, I spent all my summer holidays cooking at a refreshment stand'
description: 'I wouldn't be where I am today if...' In this series, Le Monde interviews a personality about a decisive moment in their life. The multi-Michelin-starred chef recalls the flavors of his childhood in the local public garden, where his parents worked.

headline: Despite destruction and death, Israelis widely support war against Iran
description: The overwhelming majority of the population supports Israel's strikes against Iran, partly because of the nuclear threat but also the hope for regional peace if the regime in Tehran collapses.
